OpenSCAD Polygon Editor
=======================

A web-based visual editor for OpenSCAD `polygon([...])` data. Paste your
OpenSCAD code, drag points around, and the source updates live.

OpenSCAD itself is a scripted CAD tool: http://www.openscad.org/

Original project: https://github.com/daid/OpenSCAD-polygon-editor

Usage
-----
Recommended (full feature set, including overwrite-in-place save):

    cd OpenSCAD-polygon-editor
    python3 -m http.server 8000
    # then open http://localhost:8000/index.html in Chrome / Edge

Quick peek only:

    open index.html directly (file://) — the page still works, BUT the
    File System Access API is disabled on file:// (browser security
    requirement), so "保存" will download a new copy instead of overwriting
    the bound .oscad file. The project panel surfaces a red warning in
    that case. Use the http://localhost path for real work.

Tools
-----
- Edit (E)   — Select and drag points. Click again on a smooth point's
               control points to drag handles.
- Add  (A)   — Click on the grid to append a point to the current path.
- Rem  (R)   — Click a point to delete it.
- Image (I)  — Load an image to trace over (URL or local file).

Path-point types (with Edit tool active):
- Corner — straight segments between neighbors.
- Smooth — Bezier control points that you can drag.

Features
--------
- Undo / redo                       (Ctrl/Cmd+Z, Ctrl+Y or Ctrl+Shift+Z)
- Zoom                              (Ctrl/Cmd+wheel, +/- keys, 0 to reset)
- Snap to grid toggle
- Adjustable grid size
- Keyboard delete for selected point (Del / Backspace)
- Copy code to clipboard
- Clear all paths
- Dark / light theme toggle (persisted)
- Live SVG drawing area, responsive to window resize
- Trace image overlay (URL or local file)

3D Preview
----------
Toggle "Enable 3D" in the toolbox to open a live 3D viewport beside the 2D
editor. The current polygons are extruded into solid geometry and rendered
with Three.js + OrbitControls (drag to orbit, scroll to zoom, right-drag to
pan).

Two extrusion modes:
- Linear extrude — height + optional twist (deg) and end-scale.
- Rotate extrude — sweep around the Z axis with adjustable segments and
  angle (matches OpenSCAD's `rotate_extrude`).

"Copy 3D" copies generated `linear_extrude(...) polygon([...])` or
`rotate_extrude(...) polygon([...])` code, ready to paste into OpenSCAD.

Project storage
---------------
Each project is one self-contained `.oscad` file (JSON, schema `oscad-v1`)
containing name, OpenSCAD code, saved components, and timestamps. The
project panel exposes 5 file actions in two rows:

  Primary (working-file ops):
    打开…       open a .oscad and bind it as the working file
    保存         overwrite the bound file; if none, behaves like 另存为…
    另存为…     write to a new .oscad and re-bind to it

  Secondary (lifecycle + snapshot):
    重命名       rename in-app only (disk filename unchanged)
    关闭         drop from the project list (disk file untouched)
    下载副本     download a standalone .oscad copy — does NOT touch the
                 current working-file binding (use for share/backup)

The Save button lights up (accent color) whenever the project has unsaved
changes so it's obvious there's work to flush. Chrome / Edge use the File
System Access API for real overwrite-in-place. Safari / Firefox fall back
to download / file-input — Save remembers the last filename in
localStorage and re-downloads under the same name. localStorage is the
always-on snapshot for offline reload regardless of browser.

Export OBJ
----------
"导出 OBJ" in the 操作 panel saves the current scene as a triangulated
Wavefront `.obj` file (vertices, normals, faces — no materials / colors).
Viewport helpers (grid, axes, selection box, gizmo, wire-edges) are hidden
during export and restored immediately after.

Flip
----
With one object selected, "翻转 X / Y / Z" wraps it with an outer
`mirror([...])`. Click the same axis a second time to un-flip (toggle).
Flips participate in the AST undo/redo history.

Quick Align
-----------
With exactly two objects multi-selected (A first, B second), open
"快速对齐 ▾" to dock B onto one of A's six faces (+X / -X / +Y / -Y /
+Z / -Z) in one of three modes: 中心 (centers aligned), 边(min) (lowest
edges aligned), 边(max) (highest edges aligned). The algorithm uses
axis-aligned world bounding boxes (AABB) and writes the result as a
single outer `translate([...])` wrapping B; repeated applies accumulate
into that translate rather than nesting.

  Known limitation: AABBs of rotated bodies are larger than the body
  itself, so dock contact for non-axis-aligned objects may visually
  appear loose. Rotate the body into axis-alignment first if you need
  tight contact.

Dependencies
------------
- Raphael 2.3.0 — vendored under `vendor/raphael.min.js` (no CDN).
- Three.js 0.160 + OrbitControls + TransformControls + OBJExporter —
  vendored under `vendor/three/` via importmap (no CDN). Page works
  fully offline.
- No jQuery; everything else is vanilla JS / standard browser APIs.

File overview
-------------
- index.html — page layout
- style.css  — modern theme (CSS variables, light/dark)
- osped.js   — 2D polygon editor logic + OspedAPI bridge
- three3d.js — 3D viewport (ES module)
- project.js — project + component management (.oscad single-file backend)
- openscad.js — OpenSCAD-subset parser, evaluator, AST helpers
- vendor/    — pinned third-party assets, no network needed
- tests/     — Playwright e2e suite (npm test)
